fields.title: Tulip of Joy
fields.description: With about 75 species, the Tulip is known for its bright, bulbous flowers and elegant stems. Producing one flower per stem, Tulips come in a dazzling array of colors from reds to pinks to violets and make for gorgeous bouquets inside your home.

fields.title: White Indoors
fields.description: The elegant Gaura features dainty white or pink blooms. Thriving in a variety of soil types, the Gaura is known to quickly take over gardens and be difficult to trim downâ€”so don't let your garden go unmanaged for too long!

fields.title: Loving You
fields.description: Know for its small, cloud-like blooms, this sun-loving flower makes for a great addition to rock gardens. Often cascading over rocks or walls, the Evergreen Candytuft is ideal for a filler in containers or to act as a border.

fields.title: A Gift 4U
fields.description: These sweet flowers get their name from the up-side-down hanging blooms that resemble pants. Dutchman's Breeches are one of the few flowers whose seeds are spread by ants, so don't fret if you see a colony nearby

fields.title: Granny's Bonnet
fields.description: Columbine comes from the Latin word "dove" because the shape of the inverted flower resembles doves clustered together

fields.title: Castor Bean
fields.description: This popular feline plant's grey-green leaves and lavender flowers make a beautiful garden addition. It's also easy to care for, tolerating drier climates and full sun.

fields.title: Blackeyed Susan collection
fields.description: Blackeyed Susans are a member of the sunflower family  bearing heart shaped flowers that hang from a long stem

fields.title: Bee Balm
fields.description: this ornamental flower attracts not only bees, but hummingbirds and other beneficial pollinators

fields.title: Ageratum Flossflower
fields.description: Ageratums come in blue, pink and white blooms. The taller varieties are best for cutting and displaying in your home, while the dwarf bedding varieties are best kept in the garden

fields.title: Aconite Mornings
fields.description: Aconites are one of the first bulb flowers to bloom in the spring and are known for their cheerful yellow color. Plant Aconites in a large group together and you'll be able to smell their sweet, honey-like fragrance.

fields.title: Genoise

fields.title: Angel Food Cake
fields.description: This type is made with egg whites alone and no yolks. The whites are whipped with sugar until very firm before the flour is gently folded in, resulting in a snowy-white, airy, and delicate cake that marries beautifully with fruit

fields.title: Butter (and Oil) Layer Cakes
fields.description: These cakes are usually very lightly flavored and served plain or topped with a simple glaze or water icing.

fields.title: Pound Cakes
fields.description: This is the simplest type of butter cake. A classic pound cake is made with a pound each of butter, sugar, eggs, and flour. This produces a dense yet tender texture.
